Description: Side-wall of a rectangular wooden coffin; painted eye-panel and Hieroglyphic text on a layer of plaster on the exterior side.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: The long boards show ancient repairs. The top of the edges are painted red.
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 114-115.)
